1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,740
chapter number one, and we've been studying

2
00:00:02,740 --> 00:00:04,440
on Sunday mornings here in our church

3
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:06,880
through the book of 1st and 2nd Timothy.

4
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:08,779
You see the banners on the wall behind me.

5
00:00:08,779 --> 00:00:11,380
Our theme for this year is continue,

6
00:00:11,380 --> 00:00:13,960
and this morning being Friend Day,

7
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:15,260
I was praying about where to go,

8
00:00:15,260 --> 00:00:17,680
and the Lord led me here to the book of Ephesians.

9
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:19,760
It's a wonderful book, the book of Ephesians,

10
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:22,260
and here in this book, we find that God

11
00:00:22,260 --> 00:00:24,520
helps the people of God, his children,

12
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:27,899
to understand their position in Christ.

13
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,739
We find the first three chapters really deal with that,

14
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:32,299
and in the last half of the book,

15
00:00:32,299 --> 00:00:34,479
the last three chapters deal with our walk,

16
00:00:34,479 --> 00:00:36,299
now that we're saved, here's how we live,

17
00:00:36,299 --> 00:00:38,939
here's how we behave, and what a blessing

18
00:00:38,939 --> 00:00:42,139
to know this wonderful book and the truth

19
00:00:42,139 --> 00:00:43,659
that's contained therein.

20
00:00:43,659 --> 00:00:46,720
We find that the apostle Paul had a brief stop

21
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:48,900
in the city of Ephesus near the end

22
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,479
of his second missionary journey.

23
00:00:50,479 --> 00:00:52,819
You could read of that in Acts chapter 18,

24
00:00:52,819 --> 00:00:55,340
and verses 18 and 19, and we find that

25
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:57,639
as he was briefly held in Ephesus,

26
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,959
that there was a request by those in Ephesus

27
00:00:59,959 --> 00:01:03,439
that he stay longer, but he had a need to depart,

28
00:01:03,439 --> 00:01:05,519
and we find that he said to them

29
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:09,019
that he would return if the Lord allowed,

30
00:01:09,019 --> 00:01:11,360
and we find that during the third missionary journey,

31
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:14,000
as it's recorded for us in Acts 19,

32
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,519
that the apostle Paul had the opportunity

33
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:18,220
to return to the city of Ephesus.

34
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,099
In fact, he ministered there for about three years,

35
00:01:21,099 --> 00:01:24,040
and during those three years that he's in Ephesus,

36
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:27,199
we're told that all of those within Asia Minor

37
00:01:27,199 --> 00:01:30,239
heard the word of the Lord, and what a blessing

38
00:01:30,239 --> 00:01:33,419
to think about the ministry that God gave

39
00:01:33,419 --> 00:01:36,360
for the apostle Paul there in Ephesus.

40
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:38,519
I believe that as you look at the 19th chapter

41
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:41,699
of the book of Acts, that there in the city of Ephesus,

42
00:01:41,699 --> 00:01:43,239
they experienced revival.

43
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:44,879
There were many people that were saved,

44
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:48,239
and many people that just got serious

45
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:51,919
about living for the Lord and serving the Lord,

46
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:54,599
and we find that Paul eventually would have to leave

47
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:59,599
from Ephesus and various reasons concerning his departure,

48
00:01:59,879 --> 00:02:03,360
but we find that Timothy was left to minister there

49
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,080
at the church at Ephesus.

50
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,699
In fact, as we've studied in 1 and 2 Timothy,

51
00:02:07,699 --> 00:02:10,479
those that have been with us throughout this calendar year,

52
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:12,960
you find that many times we have referenced

53
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:16,800
how the apostle Paul is providing instruction to Timothy

54
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:20,360
with regard to the ministry there in Ephesus.

55
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:22,279
We find that there's a period of time

56
00:02:22,279 --> 00:02:26,160
that passes between Paul's departure and this letter

57
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:28,360
that is called the book of Ephesians

58
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:31,080
being written to these individuals.

59
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,880
We find that in verse number one, he refers to them,

60
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:37,039
notice with me, it says, Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ,

61
00:02:37,039 --> 00:02:41,800
by the will of God, to the saints which are at Ephesus

62
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:44,479
and to the faithful in Christ Jesus.

63
00:02:44,479 --> 00:02:48,039
Grace be to you and peace from God our Father

64
00:02:48,039 --> 00:02:50,440
and from the Lord Jesus Christ.

65
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,000
It's interesting as the apostle Paul,

66
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,600
those to whom he is writing,

67
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,399
he refers to them as being saints,

68
00:02:55,399 --> 00:02:59,240
and we find that he addresses in the opening statements

69
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,600
of Ephesians chapter number one in these first

70
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,960
several verses, he deals with the important subject,

71
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,639
vital subject of redemption.

72
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:10,880
And this subject is so vital, it's so important.

73
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:14,240
In fact, because we find that the apostle Paul,

74
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:17,880
when he went to Ephesus and he preached the gospel,

75
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:19,759
there were people that got saved,

76
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:22,080
therefore they were redeemed.

77
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:25,720
And we find that Paul is rehearsing once again,

78
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:29,199
the subject of redemption, but because they were redeemed,

79
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:32,360
they're being referred to as saints.

80
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,720
And don't let that word confuse you.

81
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:37,479
There are many today that use it differently

82
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:39,720
than what we find in the scriptures.

83
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:43,199
And God uses the word saint to refer to those

84
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:46,759
who are in Christ, one in whom Christ dwells.

85
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:50,440
Again, somebody that is saved by the grace of God.

86
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,279
This morning, I wanna preach a message to you

87
00:03:52,279 --> 00:03:55,119
that I've simply entitled from these first few verses,

88
00:03:55,119 --> 00:03:58,440
redemption through his blood.

89
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,520
By the way, there's only one way to be redeemed,

90
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:03,199
and that is through the blood of the Lord Jesus Christ.

91
00:04:03,199 --> 00:04:05,679
And we find that here in this text of scripture,

92
00:04:05,679 --> 00:04:08,160
he deals with that subject of redemption.

93
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:11,279
Let me give you a definition of the word redemption.

94
00:04:11,279 --> 00:04:15,240
It's this, the purchase of God's favor

95
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:19,760
by the death and sufferings of Christ.

96
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:22,679
The purchase of God's favor

97
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:26,000
by the death and sufferings of Christ,

98
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,880
the ransom or the deliverance of sinners

99
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:33,160
from the bondage of sin and the penalties

100
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:38,040
of God's violated law by the atonement of Jesus Christ.

101
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,320
What a great definition.

102
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,440
That's right in the Webster's Dictionary,

103
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:44,160
1828 Webster's Dictionary, it's right there.

104
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:47,640
And what a great definition for the word redemption.

105
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:48,839
You understand this morning

106
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:52,000
that there is a universal condition of mankind

107
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,760
that man is born a sinner.

108
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,640
The Bible teaches us that all have sinned

109
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:58,480
and come short of the glory of God.

110
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:02,959
And because of that, man is under the penalty

111
00:05:02,959 --> 00:05:05,160
of breaking God's law.

112
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,880
And we find that because of that,

113
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:10,600
man stands in need of redemption.

114
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,920
It's a universal condition.

115
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,399
Every human being outside of the Lord Jesus Christ,

116
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:17,399
who is God in flesh,

117
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:21,160
that has walked upon the face of this earth is a sinner.

118
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:23,959
And they're in need of redemption.

119
00:05:23,959 --> 00:05:26,480
I'm so thankful that our God loves

120
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:31,480
and our God desires to save, to redeem his creation.

121
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:34,000
In fact, we find that as we look at the text of scripture,

122
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,399
begin reading with me in verse number three, if you will,

123
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:37,239
the Bible says,

124
00:05:37,239 --> 00:05:41,399
Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,

125
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:45,799
who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings

126
00:05:45,799 --> 00:05:48,559
in heavenly places in Christ,

127
00:05:48,559 --> 00:05:51,359
according as he hath chosen us in him

128
00:05:51,359 --> 00:05:53,239
before the foundation of the world,

129
00:05:53,239 --> 00:05:56,160
that we should not, or excuse me,

130
00:05:56,160 --> 00:06:00,359
that we should be holy and without blame before him in love,

131
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:04,320
having predestinated us unto the adoption of children

132
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:07,799
by Jesus Christ to himself,

133
00:06:07,799 --> 00:06:11,519
according to the good pleasure of his will.

134
00:06:11,519 --> 00:06:14,959
Verse six, to the praise of the glory of his grace,

135
00:06:14,959 --> 00:06:19,519
wherein he hath made us accepted in the beloved,

136
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:22,359
in whom we have redemption through his blood,

137
00:06:22,359 --> 00:06:24,480
the forgiveness of sins,

138
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:28,760
according to the riches of his grace.

139
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,399
If you're taking notes this morning,

140
00:06:30,399 --> 00:06:32,440
I want you to notice with me, number one,

141
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,119
the plan of redemption,

142
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,040
the plan of redemption.

143
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:39,720
I'm so thankful that God has a plan,

144
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,359
and I'm thankful that God's plan,

145
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:43,440
though throughout the centuries,

146
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,600
we find throughout human history

147
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,600
that the enemy tried to overthrow the plan of God,

148
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,640
that God's plan is perfect,

149
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,559
and God's plan is revealed to us here

150
00:06:53,559 --> 00:06:55,679
in Ephesians chapter number one.

151
00:06:55,679 --> 00:06:56,839
We find that, of course,

152
00:06:56,839 --> 00:07:00,160
the truth of redemption is throughout the entirety

153
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,119
of God's word,

154
00:07:01,119 --> 00:07:04,359
and we see the thought of redemption interwoven

155
00:07:04,359 --> 00:07:06,320
throughout the pages of Scripture,

156
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:10,160
but here in just a few verses of Scripture,

157
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:14,000
God gives us the plan of redemption.

158
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,880
It's important that we understand

159
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,920
when we consider the plan of redemption

160
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:22,079
that God determined that redemption would be possible

161
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:25,320
only through the Lord Jesus Christ.

162
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:28,279
That was what God determined,

163
00:07:28,279 --> 00:07:30,239
and in fact, He determined this

164
00:07:30,239 --> 00:07:32,600
before the foundation of the world.

165
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:35,640
Notice in verse number four, the Bible says this,

166
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:38,640
according as He hath chosen us in Him

167
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:41,839
before the foundation of the world,

168
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:44,359
that we should be holy and without blame

169
00:07:44,359 --> 00:07:45,799
before Him in love,

170
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:49,079
having predestinated us into the adoption of children,

171
00:07:49,079 --> 00:07:49,920
how?

172
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,880
By Jesus Christ to Himself,

173
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:56,079
according to the good pleasure of His will,

174
00:07:56,119 --> 00:07:57,600
and we find that oftentimes

175
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:01,440
this first introduction section of Ephesians

176
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,440
many times is confused

177
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:05,359
because there's some words that are used

178
00:08:05,359 --> 00:08:07,880
that we do not have to be afraid of these words.

179
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:10,079
We do not have to be concerned about those

180
00:08:10,079 --> 00:08:12,880
that might use these words in a different manner,

181
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,320
but we really find that what God is dealing with

182
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:18,359
in Ephesians one is really not so much

183
00:08:18,359 --> 00:08:23,359
the who of redemption, but the how of redemption.

184
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:26,760
He's not talking about who would be redeemed.

185
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:31,279
He's speaking about how mankind can be redeemed,

186
00:08:31,279 --> 00:08:32,320
and let me say this.

187
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,119
God determined before the foundation of the world

188
00:08:35,119 --> 00:08:38,320
that redemption would only be possible

189
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,080
through the Lord Jesus Christ.

190
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,159
There's no other way.

191
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:45,080
In fact, Jesus said this, John 14 in verse number six.

192
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:50,080
He said, I am the way, the truth, and the life.

193
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:55,080
No man cometh unto the Father but by me.

194
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:58,679
We find that Peter who heard the Lord Jesus Christ

195
00:08:58,679 --> 00:09:01,000
make that statement in John 14

196
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,440
that he stands up and he's preaching

197
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:06,159
as he's being questioned and interrogated

198
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:10,039
by the religious leaders in Acts chapter four,

199
00:09:10,039 --> 00:09:12,359
and he says there's no other name under heaven

200
00:09:12,359 --> 00:09:14,719
given among men whereby we must be saved.

201
00:09:14,719 --> 00:09:15,559
What is that name?

202
00:09:15,559 --> 00:09:19,039
Well, that is the precious name of the Lord Jesus Christ.

203
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:22,119
It is his name, it is the work of Christ,

204
00:09:22,119 --> 00:09:24,280
the fact that he is God in flesh,

205
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:28,559
that he humbled himself and came to this sin-cursed world,

206
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:30,239
and he went to a cruel cross.

207
00:09:30,239 --> 00:09:32,520
He was buried and he rose again

208
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,640
so that we might have redemption,

209
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:38,599
and so God determined before the foundation of the world

210
00:09:38,599 --> 00:09:42,280
that salvation, redemption would only be possible

211
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,820
through the Lord Jesus Christ.

212
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:45,359
I would say it this way.

213
00:09:45,359 --> 00:09:48,140
There's only one way to be redeemed.

214
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:51,299
The songwriter said redeemed how I love to proclaim it,

215
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,780
redeemed how?

216
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:54,179
By the blood of the Lamb.

217
00:09:54,179 --> 00:09:55,659
That's the only way to be redeemed,

218
00:09:55,659 --> 00:09:58,359
and we find here that this text of Scripture

219
00:09:58,359 --> 00:10:00,020
helps us to understand.

220
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:02,740
the way that God determined.

221
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:04,520
Now the reality is that there are people,

222
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,800
in fact, some of the religious leaders of the day

223
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,140
of the Lord Jesus Christ,

224
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:11,380
and as the apostles and disciples were ministering

225
00:10:11,380 --> 00:10:13,920
and reaching the world with the gospel,

226
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,060
they obviously encountered those

227
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:18,420
that had different ideas and thoughts

228
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:20,980
and different religions, if you will.

229
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:23,960
And we find that they would preach the truth

230
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:26,540
that Jesus is the only way.

231
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:29,160
How sad it is that today,

232
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:31,480
many have been deceived in thinking that

233
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:34,620
somehow they could be redeemed on their own merit

234
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:37,280
through something that they could do.

235
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,280
And we'll get to that in just a few moments.

236
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:42,740
There's only redemption through the Lord Jesus Christ.

237
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:44,760
We find that not only did God determine

238
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:48,360
the how of salvation according to these verses

239
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:50,240
that we've looked at, verses four and five,

240
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:53,440
but we find that he determined that we would be adopted

241
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,740
into the family of God.

242
00:10:54,740 --> 00:10:56,600
Notice again in verse number five,

243
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,160
the Bible says, having predestined us,

244
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:01,020
those that are saved, those that have been redeemed,

245
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:02,500
remember he's writing to the saints

246
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,260
according to verse number one,

247
00:11:04,260 --> 00:11:09,260
unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself.

248
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:11,780
I'm so thankful to be a child of God.

249
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:14,160
I'm so thankful to be part of the family of God.

250
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:18,400
I'm adopted, hallelujah, I'm a child of the king.

251
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:21,640
And what a joy to understand that John

252
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:24,180
in chapter number one and verse number 12 says,

253
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:27,840
but as many as received him, to them gave he power

254
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,440
to become the sons of God,

255
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:32,040
even to them that believe on his name.

256
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:35,320
And we find this morning that we understand

257
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,100
that we've been, if you're saved this morning,

258
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:40,280
if you've been redeemed, you're part of the family of God.

259
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,120
What does that mean?

260
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:43,080
Well, it means that God's my father.

261
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,760
It means that I'm his child.

262
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:47,000
It means that I'll spend forever with him

263
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:51,240
